{
  "text": "Patients were instructed to stop caffeine intake 24 h before the procedure as caffeine is considered as adenosine receptor antagonist that may interfere with adenosine-induced hyperemia and affects FFR results [CITATION_1] . No anesthesia was required. Access: routine trans-femoral or trans-radial approach for cardiac catheterization was applied. Diagnostic coronary angiography was done with localization of the site of stenosis of interest. Calibration of pressure systems: the pressure lines were flushed with saline. Then, the \"zeroreference\" was recorded.",
